## Local dev

Per-runtime setup (install, run, first-time gotchas) lives in
`.claude/runtimes/<name>.md`. The goal is still "new contributor
can clone and be running in 10 minutes" — but each runnable thing
documents itself in its own stamp, so multi-runtime projects (API
+ web + worker) don't have to cram everything into one prose blob.

{{TOP-LEVEL OVERVIEW ONLY: e.g. "Clone, then for each runtime in
`.claude/runtimes/`, follow its First-time setup section. Order
matters: start dependencies (postgres, redis) first, then the
runtimes that depend on them."}}

